Maintainer: Thomas Fillon <thomas.fillon@univ-ubs.fr>
Description: kernopt is an package that implements the discrete symmetric optimal kernel for estimating count data distributions as proposed by T. Senga Kiessé and G. Durrieu (2024). The package provides a function to compute this optimal discrete symmetric kernel together with three other discrete associated kernels function: the Epanechnikov, the triangular and the binomial kernels. A generic discrete kernel function wraps together these four kernel functions. In addition to the choice of discrete kernel, the choice of the bandwidth parameter is challenging. The package propose a cross-validation method for selecting the smoothing bandwidth parameter to be used with the different discrete kernels. A discrete kernel density estimation fiinction with these kernels is also provide.
